  <setup>
    <selectFromSequence name="a" from="2" to="5" step="1"/>
    <selectFromSequence name="b" from="2" to="5" step="1" exclude="$a"/>
    <selectFromSequence name="c" from="4" to="7" step="1" exclude="$a $b"/>
    <selectFromSequence name="d" from="4" to="7" step="1" exclude="$a $b $c"/>

    <number name="P">($a^2-$c*$a+$d)/($a^2+$b^2)</number>
    <number name="Q">($d-$P*($c^2+$b^2))/($c*($c-$a)) - $R/$c</number>   
    <number name="R">($d-$P*$b^2)/(-$a)</number>

    <mathList name="PFdecomp">$P/(x-$a) $Q/(x-$b)</mathList>
    <mathList name="PFdecompEntered">$PF1 $PF2</mathList>
    
    <function name="f" symbolic="false" >
      (x^2 - $c*x+$d)/((x-$a)*(x^2+$b^2))
    </function> 

    <function name="F" symbolic="false" >
      $P*ln(abs(x-$a)) + $Q/2*ln(abs(x^2+$b^2)) + $R/$b*atan(x/$b)
    </function>   

    <function name="F1" symbolic="false" >
      $P*ln(abs(x-$a)) + $Q/2*ln(x^2+$b^2) + $R/$b*atan(x/$b)
    </function>  

    <boolean name="correctPFfound">$PFfound.creditAchieved=1</boolean>
    
  </setup>

<p>
  Consider the indefinite integral
  <me>
    \int \frac{x^2 - $c x + $d}{(x-$a)(x^2+<math simplify>$b^2</math>)} \, dx
  </me>
  We want to evaluate this integral using the method of partial fractions.
</p>
 

<p>
  First, the partial fraction decomposition of the integrand has the following form:
  <me>
    \frac{x^2 - $c x + $d}{(x-$a)(x^2+<math simplify>$b^2</math>)} = \frac{A}{x-$a} + \frac{Bx+C}{x^2 + <math simplify>$b^2</math>}
  </me>
  Determine the values of <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>, and <m>C</m> and enter them in the spaces provided
</p>  

<p>
  <m>A = </m> <mathInput minWidth="40" name="Aentered"/>, <m>B = </m>  <mathInput minWidth="40" name="Bentered"/>, <m>C = </m> <mathInput minWidth="40" name="Centered"/> <answer name="PFfound"><award><when>$Aentered = $P and $Bentered = $Q and $Centered = $R</when></award></answer>
</p>  

<p hide="$correctPFfound">
  (<em>Once you have the correct values of <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>, and <m>C</m> above, additional prompts will appear.</em>)
</p>
<p hide="not $correctPFfound">
  <p>
    By writing <m>\frac{Bx+C}{x^2 + <math simplify>$b^2</math>} = \frac{Bx}{x^2 + <math simplify>$b^2</math>} + \frac{C}{x^2 + <math simplify>$b^2</math>}</m> and using the numerical values for <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>, and <m>C</m> from above, we now have three integrals to evaluate in order to evaluate the full original integral.  That is,
  </p>
  <p>
    <m>\displaystyle \int \frac{x^2 - $c x + $d}{(x-$a)(x^2+<math simplify>$b^2</math>)} dx = \int \frac{$P}{x-$a} dx + \int \frac{$Q x}{x^2 + <math simplify>$b^2</math>} dx + \int \frac{$R}{x^2 + <math simplify>$b^2</math>}  </m>
  </p>  
  <p>
    Evaluate each of the three integrals appropriately and fill in the results below to find the overall result of evaluating the original indefinite integral.
  </p>
  <p>
    <m>\displaystyle \int \frac{x^2 - $c x + $d}{(x-$a)(x^2+<math simplify>$b^2</math>)} dx = </m>  <mathInput name="int1"/> <m> \displaystyle +  </m> <mathInput name="int2"/> <m> \displaystyle  + </m> <mathInput name="int3"/> <m> + \, C \, </m> <answer><award><when>((<math>$int1 + $int2 + $int3</math>) = $F) or ((<math>$int1 + $int2 + $int3</math>) = $F1)</when></award></answer>
  </p> 

</p>